Cloud deployment is expected to dominate the market as it offers scalability, flexibility, and cost-effectiveness, making it a preferred choice for businesses looking to adopt digital transformation initiatives. Large enterprises are anticipated to have a significant market share due to their higher IT budgets and resources to invest in comprehensive digital transformation strategies. On the other hand, small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) are also increasingly recognizing the importance of digital transformation to remain competitive and meet evolving customer demands.

In terms of verticals, sectors such as banking, financial services, and insurance (BFSI), healthcare, IT and telecommunications, retail, and manufacturing are driving the growth of the digital transformation market. The BFSI sector, in particular, is witnessing substantial growth as organizations in this industry adopt digital technologies to improve customer engagement, enhance security measures, and optimize operational efficiency. The healthcare sector is also undergoing a digital transformation to improve patient care, streamline administrative processes, and enable better data-driven decision-making.

